div1.p: In The United States Circuit Court, For the Ninth Juidicial Circuit, Western Division of the State of Washington, Northern Division.
In re. Parte: Turner Jackson, Petitioner, No. 1325.

Comes now the United States Attorney for the Western District of Washington and duly excepts to the order of discharge made and entered in the above en- titled matter on this 11th day of September 1905: for the reason and upon the grounds following, to-wit:
That said order of discharge is not supported by the law controlling in the premises.
That said order of discharge is contrary to the facts of the premises.
That said order of discharge is not warranted by nor supported by the facts, nor by the law in the premises. Jesse A. Frye. United States Attorney.
Which exceptions are allowed this day. C.H. Hanford, Judge.
